"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with this code is that it tries to access and modify a figure after it has been closed. In Matplotlib, once a figure is closed, it is no longer accessible. So, when the code tries to get the active figure after closing it, it will return None. Even if the figure was not closed, trying to add text to an axis after the figure has been displayed with show() can lead to unexpected behavior because the figure is already displayed.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8d7\\n< plt.close()\\n---\\n\\n16c15\\n< plt.show(block=False)\\n< plt.close()\\n---\\n> ac_fig.show(block=False)\\n\"\n}"